# --- This project's model artifacts ---
# `models/` IS tracked so small fitted artifacts (e.g. a pickled TfidfVectorizer,
# typically <1 MB on this corpus) can be committed via `save_model(...)`.
# Notes:
#   - GitHub's hard limit is 100 MB / file. For anything bigger, use Git LFS
#     or attach the artifact to a GitHub Release.
#   - Do NOT commit downloaded foundation models (word2vec-google-news-300,
#     all-MiniLM-L6-v2). They live in user caches and are pinned by name in code.
# If you want to keep an empty `models/` folder tracked, add `models/.gitkeep`.

# --- Gradio ---
# Local cache of flagged / uploaded examples created by iface.launch(...)
flagged/
gradio_cached_examples/
.gradio/

# --- ML model caches (only if a user moves them into the repo) ---
# Defaults live under ~/.cache or ~/gensim-data, but ignore in-tree copies just in case
gensim-data/
.cache/
sentence-transformers/
huggingface/
.huggingface/

# --- NLTK data (ignore only if dropped inside the repo) ---
nltk_data/

# --- Notebooks: large outputs / converted exports ---
*.html
*.nbconvert.ipynb

